headline: Hormel Foods (NYSE:HRL) Posts Q3 Sales In Line With Estimates But Full-Year Sales Guidance Misses Expectations
summary: Packaged foods company Hormel (NYSE:HRL) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2024, but sales fell by 1.9% year on year to $3.14 billion. On the other hand, the company’s full-year revenue guidance of $12.05 billion at the midpoint came in 1.6% below analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.42 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.
